data.text:
ello all

I still cant believe Melbourne are on top dank!!!

Got some news from around the grounds...

Adelaide United are in the box seat to snag Romario

Shegging Qu coped a two match ban for his headbutt

Damian Mori will be with CCM with a 4 week contract - starting with tommorow's game against New Zealand (well they do need to score goals )

oh and btw - Australia has sorted its squad for its friendlies in brisbane, sydney and bahrain

it includes 20 of Oz world cup stars plus 8 of a-leauge's fines...

Socceroo World Cup stars reunite

John Aloisi (Alaves, Spain), Michael Beauchamp (Nuremberg, Germany), Alex Brosque (Sydney FC, Australia), Marco Bresciano (Palermo, Italy), Tim Cahill (Everton, England), Scott Chipperfield (Basel, Switzerland), Ante Covic (Hammarby, Sweden), Jason Culina (PSV Eindhoven The Netherlands), Travis Dodd (Adelaide United, Australia), Brett Emerton (Blackburn Rovers, England), Vince Grella (Parma, Italy), Zeljko Kalac (AC Milan, Italy),Stan Lazaridis (Perth Glory, Australia), Mark Milligan (Sydney FC, Australia), Craig Moore (Newcastle United, England), Lucas Neill (Blackburn Rovers, England), Tony Popovic (Al-Arabi, Qatar), Mark Schwarzer (Middlesbrough, England), Josip Skoko (Wigan Athletic, England), Mile Sterjovski (Basle, Switzerland), Archie Thompson (Melbourne Victory, Australia), Tony Vidmar (Central Coast Mariners, Australia) ( ), Luke Wilkshire (FC Twente, The Netherlands)

Keven Muscat and Jade North will be selected for the game in Bahrain only

Harry Kewell (ankle) and Josh Kennedy (achillies) are injured and Mark Viduka's wife is expecting and wont be in the team
